'''Michael Akpovie Olise''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɒ|'|l|i|s|eɪ}};<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 December 2023 |title=OLISE BRACE ! {{!}} Premier League Highlights Crystal Palace 3-1 Brentford |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2So4xYF-B6A&t=82s |access-date=24 December 2024 |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=[[Crystal Palace F.C.]] |archive-date=28 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241228233442/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2So4xYF-B6A&t=82s |url-status=live }}</ref> {{respell|o|LEE|say}}; {{IPA|urh|à.k͡pɔ̀.vjɛ̀ ɔ̀.lí.sɛ̀|lang|link=yes}}; {{IPA|fr|maikəl olisɛ|lang}};<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 September 2024 |title=La CONNEXION MBAPPÉ / OLISE choque tout le monde à l'entraînement des Bleus - La Quotidienne #1587 |trans-title=The MBAPPÉ / OLISE CONNECTION shocks everyone at Les Bleus training - La Quotidienne #1587 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EtIVcpcTbrw&t=97s |access-date=24 December 2024 |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=[[Téléfoot]] |language=French}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 August 2024 |title=Pourquoi Michael Olise est la NOUVELLE STAR du football français |trans-title=Why Michael Olise is the NEW STAR of French football |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q54G7tOoRGM |access-date=24 December 2024 |website=[[YouTube]] |publisher=Foot Mercato FC |language=French |archive-date=8 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241008185939/https://www.youtube.com/watch?si=mWp5B7RK2v3xfeO6&v=Q54G7tOoRGM |url-status=live }}</ref> born 12 December 2001) is a  professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] or [[attacking midfielder]] for {{German football updater|BaMunich}} club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]. Born in England, he plays for the [[France national football team|France national team]]. Considered one of the best wingers in the world, he is known for his creativity, dribbling, and flair.<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 July 2025 |title=The 25 Best Right Wingers in World Soccer—Ranked |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/the-best-right-wingers-in-world-soccer-ranked |access-date=18 October 2025 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Holt |first=Mark White Contributions from Matthew |last2=Stronge |first2=Isaac Stacey |last3=published |first3=Joe Mewis |date=16 June 2025 |title=Ranked! The 10 best right-wingers in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/ranked-best-right-wingers-in-the-world |access-date=18 October 2025 |website=FourFourTwo |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Swan |first=Rob |last2=Malyan |first2=Christy |last3=Murray |first3=Will |last4=Hepburn |first4=Daniel |date=10 November 2023 |title=The 30 best footballers in the world right now - ranked in order |url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-football-players-in-the-world/ |access-date=18 October 2025 |website=GiveMeSport |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Holmes |first=Ned |title=Best wingers in the world 2025 {{!}} Radio Times |url=https://www.radiotimes.com/tv/sport/football/best-wingers-world/ |access-date=18 October 2025 |website=www.radiotimes.com |language=en-GB}}</ref>

The product of various English [[Youth system|academies]], Olise made his professional debut for [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] in 2019. In 2021, he was signed by [[Premier League]] club [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]], where he spent three seasons and was nominated for [[PFA Young Player of the Year]] in 2024, before moving to Bayern.

Olise represented France at youth level and was included in their squad for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Summer Olympics]]. He made his debut for the senior French team in September 2024.

==Early life==
Michael Akpovie Olise<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce158/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf |title=Squad List: Men's Olympic Football Tournament Paris 2024: France (FRA) |publisher=FIFA |page=4 |date=27 July 2024 |access-date=3 March 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240711134744/https://fdp.fifa.org/assetspublic/ce158/pdf/SquadLists-English.pdf |archive-date=11 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> was born on 12 December 2001<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/players/443661/michael-olise/overview |title=Michael Olise: Overview |publisher=Premier League |access-date=7 June 2026}}</ref> in [[White City, London|White City]], Greater London, England, and raised in [[Hayes, Hillingdon|Hayes]], Greater London,<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=9 October 2021 |title=Linked-up: How Palace's generation of local talent grew up connected - News |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/first-team/how-crystal-palaces-local-players-eze-olise-mitchell-and-others-are-connected/ |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Crystal Palace F.C. |language=en-GB |archive-date=23 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240623214301/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/first-team/how-crystal-palaces-local-players-eze-olise-mitchell-and-others-are-connected/ |url-status=live }}</ref> to a [[British Nigerian|British-Nigerian]] father and [[Algerians in France|Franco-Algerian]] mother.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Silas |first=Don |date=4 September 2024 |title='My mother is from France' - Olise on why he snubbed Nigeria, England, Algeria |url=https://dailypost.ng/2024/09/04/my-mother-is-from-france-olise-on-why-he-snubbed-nigeria-england-algeria/ |location=Lagos, Nigeria|access-date=5 April 2025 |newspaper=[[Daily Post (Nigeria)|Daily Post]]|language=en-US |archive-date=10 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240910113312/https://dailypost.ng/2024/09/04/my-mother-is-from-france-olise-on-why-he-snubbed-nigeria-england-algeria/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In an interview with the Bayern magazine ''51'', when asked about his nationality, he said: "I actually come from four countries: France, Algeria, Nigeria and England. I consider myself very lucky to possess these four parts, which all enrich me. I feel each individual part in me, I've developed attachments in all my countries."<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |date=27 December 2024|title=Michael Olise interview - 'I want to make history with this team' |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2024/12/michael-olise-interview |access-date=21 April 2025 |website=FC Bayern München |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Olise joined [[Hayes & Yeading United F.C.|Hayes & Yeading United]] around the age of six, before briefly joining [[Arsenal F.C. Under-21s and Academy|Arsenal]] and then moving to [[Chelsea F.C. Academy|Chelsea Academy]].<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7254915/2026/05/06/michael-olise-the-making-of/ |title=The making of Michael Olise: The quiet kid who came alive on the pitch |publisher=The New York Times |date=6 May 2026 }}</ref> He spent seven years with Chelsea before leaving at the age of 14, and also had a youth spell with [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=De Cosemo |first=Harry |date=16 April 2022 |title=Michael Olise: Crystal Palace winger's path from Chelsea released to Eagles star |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61111925 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=6 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230406043616/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61111925 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Reading===
In July 2018, Olise was inducted into [[Reading F.C.|Reading]]'s Academy scholarship program.<ref>{{Cite web |last=FC |first=Reading |title=12 youngsters inducted onto Academy scholarships |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/12-youngsters-inducted-onto-academy-scholarships/ |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Reading FC |archive-date=5 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211005045644/https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/12-youngsters-inducted-onto-academy-scholarships/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=17 August 2023 |title=Michael Olise: Who be di France player wit Nigerian roots Chelsea wan sign for £35m |url=https://www.bbc.com/pidgin/articles/c89r7vwz55go |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=BBC News Pidgin |archive-date=21 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241221031914/https://www.bbc.com/pidgin/articles/c89r7vwz55go |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his debut for [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] on 12 March 2019, in a 3–0 home defeat to [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]],<ref>{{cite web |title=East and Olise presented with framed debut shirts |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/march/east-and-olise-presented-with-framed-debut-shirts/ |work=Reading F.C. |access-date=27 May 2019 |date=23 March 2019 |archive-date=27 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190527192224/https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/march/east-and-olise-presented-with-framed-debut-shirts/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and on 15 July, he signed a three-year professional contract with the club.<ref>{{Cite web |last=FC |first=Reading |title=Olise signs three-year professional deal with the Royals |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/july/olise-signs-three-year-professional-deal-with-the-royals |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Reading FC |archive-date=15 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190715140631/https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/july/olise-signs-three-year-professional-deal-with-the-royals |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first league goal for Reading on 19 September 2020, volleying home in the 76th minute with the second goal in a 2–0 win over [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] at the [[Madejski Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=19 September 2020 |title=Reading 2-0 Barnsley: Royals overcome nine-man Tykes |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54127590 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=19 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919212128/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54127590 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In April 2021 he was nominated for the EFL Young Player of the Season.<ref>{{Cite news |date=26 April 2021 |title=EFL Awards: Norwich's Emi Buendia wins Championship player of the season award |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56893266 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=24 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210724172910/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/56893266 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=FC |first=Reading |date=26 April 2021 |title=👏 Olise nominated for EA Sports Young Player of the Season award |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2021/april/-olise-nominated-for-ea-sports-young-player-of-the-season-award/ |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Reading FC}}</ref> On 29 April 2021, he was crowned EFL Young Player of the Season.<ref>{{Cite news |date=26 April 2021 |title=EFL Awards: Norwich's Emi Buendia wins Championship player of the season award |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56893266 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=22 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211022173830/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56893266 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Crystal Palace===
[[File:Olise 2022 crystal palace.jpg|thumb|upright|Olise in 2022]]

On 8 July 2021, Olise signed a five-year deal with [[Premier League]] side [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] after they had activated his £8.37 million release clause.<ref>{{Cite news |date=7 July 2021 |title=Michael Olise: Crystal Palace close to signing Reading forward |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57746533 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 11 September, he made his Premier League debut for the club in a 3–0 home win against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] after coming on as a substitute in the 86th minute in place of [[Jordan Ayew]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=11 September 2021 |title=Crystal Palace 3-0 Tottenham Hotspur: Eagles beat leaders Spurs for first win of league campaign |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58436965 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=11 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210911174137/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58436965 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Low |first=Jonathan |date=13 September 2021|title=Patrick Vieira says Michael Olise must show he's a team player at Crystal Palace |url=https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/patrick-vieira-reading-michael-olise-21553182 |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Berkshire Live |language=en |archive-date=25 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220125230626/https://www.getreading.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/patrick-vieira-reading-michael-olise-21553182 |url-status=live }}</ref> Later that month, on 23 September, Olise made his full debut for Crystal Palace in a 1–1 home draw against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=23 September 2021 |title=Crystal Palace 1-1 Newcastle: Callum Wilson overhead kick rescues point for Graeme Jones' Magpies |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58936300 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=27 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211027101154/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58936300 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Crystal Palace vs. Newcastle United – 23 October 2021 – Soccerway|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/10/23/england/premier-league/crystal-palace-fc/newcastle-united-football-club/3517135/|access-date=25 January 2022|website=uk.soccerway.com|archive-date=25 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220125230617/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/10/23/england/premier-league/crystal-palace-fc/newcastle-united-football-club/3517135/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 3 October 2021, Olise scored his first Premier League goal for the club as a second-half substitute in a 2–2 home draw against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=3 October 2021 |title=Crystal Palace 2-2 Leicester City Palace fight back to salvage draw |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58667896 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=20 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211020055959/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58667896 |url-status=live }}</ref> In doing so he became Palace's youngest Premier League scorer since [[Clinton Morrison]] in 1998.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wyatt |first=Mark |date=5 October 2021 |title=Patrick Vieira says Michael Olise still needs time to develop |url=https://www.football.london/crystal-palace-fc/crystal-palace-michael-olise-vieira-21759945 |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Football London |language=en |archive-date=5 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211005073218/https://www.football.london/crystal-palace-fc/crystal-palace-michael-olise-vieira-21759945 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 9 April 2023, Olise became the youngest player to assist three goals from open play in a single Premier League match in a 5–1 victory against Leeds United.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/leeds-vs-c-palace/report/464928|title=Leeds United 1–5 Crystal Palace|website=Sky Sports|date=10 April 2023|access-date=13 April 2023|archive-date=18 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230418015432/https://www.skysports.com/football/leeds-vs-c-palace/report/464928|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=9 April 2023 |title=📈 Palace starlet makes history with hat-trick of assists |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/palace-starlet-makes-history-with-hat-trick-of-assists-37160175 |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=OneFootball |language=en |archive-date=10 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230410021328/https://onefootball.com/en/news/palace-starlet-makes-history-with-hat-trick-of-assists-37160175 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 13 May, he became the first Palace player to register ten assists in a single Premier League season, setting up [[Eberechi Eze]]'s second goal in a 2–0 win against [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=13 May 2023 |title=Crystal Palace 2-0 Bournemouth: Eberechi Eze enjoys new freedom as double earns Eagles victory |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65506038 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=13 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230513200149/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65506038 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 17 August 2023, it was announced Olise had signed a new four-year deal with Crystal Palace, amidst reports that he was on the verge of re-joining Chelsea.<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 August 2023 |title=Michael Olise signs new four-year contract - News |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/announcement/michael-olise-signs-new-four-year-contract/ |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Crystal Palace F.C. |language=en-GB |archive-date=17 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230817151615/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/announcement/michael-olise-signs-new-four-year-contract/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Olise suffered a [[hamstring injury]] described by Palace manager [[Roy Hodgson]] as "serious" in a 4–1 defeat by [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] on 3 February 2024, having only just come on as a substitute.<ref>{{Cite news |date=8 February 2024 |title=Michael Olise: Roy Hodgson says injury for Crystal Palace winger is 'devastating' |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68244087 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He returned from injury in April that year, which was followed by strong performances including scoring a brace in a 4–0 victory over [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 6 May.<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Woosnam |first1=Matt |last2=Tharme |first2=Liam |date=21 June 2024 |title=Michael Olise – what makes him so special? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5399490/2024/04/12/michael-olise-transfer-future-crystal-palace/ |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Aarons |first=Ed |date=6 May 2024 |title=Michael Olise works magic for Palace to deepen Manchester United's misery |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/may/06/crystal-palace-manchester-united-premier-league-match-report |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He eventually concluded the season with ten goals and six assists in just 19 appearances across the season, having been invigorated under new coach [[Oliver Glasner]], and was later nominated for [[PFA Young Player of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4038745 |title=Why Olise can have a major impact in 2024/25 Fantasy |publisher=Premier League |date=16 June 2024 |access-date=21 June 2024 |archive-date=21 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240621230341/https://www.premierleague.com/news/4038745 |url-status=live }}</ref> His impressive form attracted interest from other Premier League clubs including [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 April 2025 |title=Arsenal favourites ahead of Man Utd & Chelsea to sign Michael Olise |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/arsenal-favourites-ahead-of-man-utd-chelsea-to-sign-michael-olise-39375234 |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=OneFootball |language=en |archive-date=21 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240621230341/https://onefootball.com/en/news/arsenal-favourites-ahead-of-man-utd-chelsea-to-sign-michael-olise-39375234 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/13152596/michael-olise-chelsea-and-newcastle-approach-crystal-palace-about-signing-winger |title=Michael Olise: Chelsea and Newcastle approach Crystal Palace about signing winger |publisher=Sky Sports |date=14 June 2024 }}</ref> On 7 July, Crystal Palace announced that he had completed a permanent transfer to Bayern Munich, with Olise penning the club a farewell message on [[Instagram]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 July 2024 |title=Michael Olise departs Palace for Bayern Munich - News |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/announcement/michael-olise-departs-palace-for-bayern-munich/ |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Crystal Palace F.C. |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===Bayern Munich===
====2024–25: Debut season====
[[File:Michael Olise bayern 2025.jpg|thumb|upright|Olise playing for [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in 2025]]

On 7 July 2024, [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] announced the signing of Olise from Crystal Palace on a five-year contract valid through to 30 June 2029,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2024/07/fc-bayern-sign-michael-olise|title=FC Bayern sign Michael Olise|publisher=FC Bayern Munich|date=7 July 2024|access-date=7 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=5 April 2025 |title=FC Bayern sign Michael Olise |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/fc-bayern-sign-michael-olise-39730731 |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> for a reported transfer fee of €60m including add-ons.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11706/13174761/michael-olise-transfer-crystal-palace-forward-completes-gbp50-8m-move-to-bayern-munich |title=Michael Olise transfer: Crystal Palace forward completes £50.8m move to Bayern Munich |publisher=Sky Sports |date=8 July 2024 |access-date=8 July 2024 |archive-date=8 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240708234400/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11706/13174761/michael-olise-transfer-crystal-palace-forward-completes-gbp50-8m-move-to-bayern-munich |url-status=live }}</ref> Olise made his debut as a substitute in a 4–0 [[2024–25 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] win against [[SSV Ulm 1846|SSV Ulm]] on 16 August, registering an assist for [[Kingsley Coman]]'s goal within two minutes of entering the pitch.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fcbayern.com/en/matches/profis/dfb-pokal/2024-2025/ssv-ulm-1846-fussball-fc-bayern-muenchen-16-08-2024/report|title=Bayern down Ulm to advance to second cup round|date=16 August 2024|website=FC Bayern Munich}}</ref> On 14 September, he scored his first Bundesliga goal in a 6–1 victory over [[Holstein Kiel]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Holstein Kiel vs Bayern München: Bundesliga |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cn0ldr4ny7nt |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=18 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240918130644/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cn0ldr4ny7nt |url-status=live }}</ref> Three days later, he scored a brace, his first goals at the [[Allianz Arena]], on his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut, a 9–2 win over [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kane scores four and breaks record in Bayern rout |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cdrjlynlv8lt |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He concluded his debut season with 12 goals and 15 assists, ending as the league's top assist provider.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/olise-wirtz-top-5-assist-providers-2024-25-grifo-brandt-gross-32460 |title=Michael Olise, Florian Wirtz and the top five assist providers in 2024/25 |publisher=Bundesliga |date=29 May 2025 |access-date=5 June 2025 |archive-date=8 June 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250608050525/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/olise-wirtz-top-5-assist-providers-2024-25-grifo-brandt-gross-32460 |url-status=live }}</ref> His performances earned him a spot in the 2024–25 Bundesliga Team of the Season, as well as the league’s Rookie of the Season award.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Rookie of the Month |url=https://www.rookie-award.com/ |access-date=17 September 2025 |website=www.rookie-award.com}}</ref>

On 15 June 2025, he netted a brace in a 10–0 win against [[Auckland City FC|Auckland City]] in the opening match of the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Calcutt |first=Robert |url=https://talksport.com/football/3291073/michael-olise-bayern-munich-auckland-city-club-world-cup/ |title='Elite mentality' – Michael Olise drops brutal one-word answer to Auckland City question |publisher=talkSPORT |date=16 June 2025 |access-date=21 June 2025 |archive-date=21 June 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250621204311/https://talksport.com/football/3291073/michael-olise-bayern-munich-auckland-city-club-world-cup/ |url-status=live }}</ref> before scoring the winner in a 2–1 victory against [[Boca Juniors]], securing his club's qualification to the competition's knockout phase.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/fifa-club-world-cup/articles/bayern-munich-2-1-boca-juniors-olise-sends-kompanys-side-into-club-world-cup-knockout-phase-2025-06-21 |title=Bayern Munich 2-1 Boca Juniors: Olise sends Kompany's side into Club World Cup knockout phase |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=21 June 2025 |access-date=21 June 2025 |archive-date=21 June 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250621204310/https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/fifa-club-world-cup/articles/bayern-munich-2-1-boca-juniors-olise-sends-kompanys-side-into-club-world-cup-knockout-phase-2025-06-21 |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2025–26: Bundesliga Player of the Season award====
On 22 August 2025, Olise scored his first goals of the season by netting a brace in a 6–0 win over [[RB Leipzig]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Millington |first=Adam |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cdx042d0p0pt |title=Bayern Munich 6–0 RB Leipzig |publisher=BBC Sport |date=22 August 2025 }}</ref> On 15 April 2026, he netted a stoppage-time winner in a 4–3 triumph over [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League quarter-final]] second leg, sending his team through to the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/02a4-2065d3ad61f5-d3ad2c2b1ca9-1000--bayern-munchen-4-3-real-madrid-agg-6-4-late-goals-send-baye/ |title=Bayern München 4-3 Real Madrid (agg: 6-4): Late goals send Bayern to semi-finals in Champions League classic |publisher=UEFA |date=15 April 2026 }}</ref> A month later, on 9 May, he scored in a 1–0 away win over [[VfL Wolfsburg|Wolfsburg]], becoming only the second player since detailed records began in 2004–05 to record at least 15 goals and 15 assists in a single Bundesliga season, after [[Jadon Sancho]] in 2019–20.<ref>{{cite web |last=Brkic |first=Marko |url=https://www.spox.com/fussball/listen/das-gelang-zuvor-nur-jadon-sancho-fuer-den-bvb-michael-olise-vom-fc-bayern-erreicht-besonderen-meilenstein-in-der-bundesliga/blt03998c78e7ab6c74#cse47b09bb9df2280a |title=Das gelang zuvor nur Jadon Sancho für den BVB: Michael Olise vom FC Bayern erreicht besonderen Meilenstein in der Bundesliga |publisher=SPOX.com |language=de |date=10 May 2026 }}</ref> He was eventually voted the [[Bundesliga Awards|Bundesliga Player of the Season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcbayern.com/en/news/2026/05/michael-olise-named-bundesliga-2025-26-player-of-the-season |title=Michael Olise named Bundesliga’s 2025/26 Player of the Season |publisher=FC Bayern Munich |date=16 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Olise was born in England to a [[British Nigerian|Nigerian]] father and [[Algerians in France|Franco-Algerian]] mother, and was eligible to represent [[France national football team|France]], [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]], [[England national football team|England]] or [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] internationally.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Walters |first=Mike |date=15 January 2021 |title=Meet Michael Olise, already the Championship's most-coveted wonderkid |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/meet-michael-olise-wonderkid-whos-23328374 |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Daily Mirror |language=en |archive-date=3 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603003310/https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/meet-michael-olise-wonderkid-whos-23328374 |url-status=live }}</ref>

When asked why he chose to represent France rather than England, Olise said, "I have always had a connection with the France national team, that is why I play for France."<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 September 2024 |title="I always had a connection to France" – Michael Olise explains decision to play for France over England |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/always-had-connection-france-michael-200700254.html |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> "It's been my dream since I was a kid" to play in the French team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 September 2024 |title="J'avais cette connexion avec la France": pourquoi Olise a choisi les Bleus (alors qu'il avait le choix) |url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/equipe-de-france/j-avais-cette-connexion-avec-la-france-pourquoi-olise-a-choisi-les-bleus-alors-qu-il-avait-le-choix_AV-202409030693.html |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=RMC Sport |language=fr |archive-date=8 April 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250408144652/https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/equipe-de-france/j-avais-cette-connexion-avec-la-france-pourquoi-olise-a-choisi-les-bleus-alors-qu-il-avait-le-choix_AV-202409030693.html |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Youth===
On 27 May 2019, Olise was called up to the [[France national under-18 football team|France national under-18 team]] for the [[2019 Toulon Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Loïc Mbe Soh and Arthur Zagre with France U18 |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/the-club/content/loiec-mbe-soh-et-arthur-zagre-avec-la-france-u18-1 |website=psg.fr/ |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C. |access-date=27 May 2019 |language=French |date=27 May 2019 |archive-date=7 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230407123359/https://www.psg.fr/equipes/the-club/content/loiec-mbe-soh-et-arthur-zagre-avec-la-france-u18-1 |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his debut on 2 June 2019, against [[Qatar national under-23 football team|Qatar U23]]. In March 2021, Olise was named as a standby for the Nigeria squad taking part in their [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group L|Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers]] against [[Benin national football team|Benin]] and [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=10 March 2021 |title=Nigeria coach Gernot Rohr clarifies Ahmed Musa is non-playing captain |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/africa/56344992 |access-date=5 April 2025 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=10 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210310120239/https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/56344992 |url-status=live }}</ref> In March 2022, Olise was called up to the [[France national under-21 football team|France under-21 team]] for the first time,<ref>{{cite web |title=Michael Olise named in France Under-21s squad |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/announcement/michael-olise-named-in-france-under-21-squad-for-faroe-island-and-northern-ireland-games/2022-03-17/ |website=Crystal Palace F.C. |access-date=17 March 2022 |date=17 March 2022 |archive-date=23 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220523180634/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/announcement/michael-olise-named-in-france-under-21-squad-for-faroe-island-and-northern-ireland-games/2022-03-17/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and made his debut in the side's 2–0 win over the [[Faroe Islands national under-21 football team|Faroe Islands]] on 24 March.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Olise makes first France U21 appearance in Faroe Islands win – News |url=https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/first-team/find-out-fixtures-and-call-ups-for-crystal-palace-march-2022-internationals/2022-03-25/ |access-date=25 March 2022 |website=Crystal Palace F.C. |language=en-GB |archive-date=29 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220329064003/https://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/first-team/find-out-fixtures-and-call-ups-for-crystal-palace-march-2022-internationals/2022-03-25/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 8 July 2024, he was called up in [[France Olympic football team|France]]'s [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's team squads|final squad]] for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Paris Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Thierry Henry dévoile la liste officielle pour les JO 2024 avec quatre réservistes |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Jo-2024-paris/Football/Actualites/Thierry-henry-devoile-la-liste-officielle-pour-les-jo-2024-avec-quatre-reservistes/1480948 |website=L'Equipe |access-date=11 June 2024 |archive-date=8 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240708115807/https://www.lequipe.fr/Jo-2024-paris/Football/Actualites/Thierry-henry-devoile-la-liste-officielle-pour-les-jo-2024-avec-quatre-reservistes/1480948 |url-status=live }}</ref> He had previously received his first cap with the French Olympic team on 4 July during a friendly game against [[Paraguay national under-23 football team|Paraguay]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Premier test réussi face au Paraguay |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/12828-premier-test-reussi-face-au-paraguay-4-1-.html |website=FFF |access-date=11 June 2024}}</ref> One week later, on 11 July, he scored his first two goals during another friendly match, a 7–0 win against the [[Dominican Republic national under-23 football team|Dominican Republic]].<ref>{{cite web |title=L'équipe de France olympique corrige la République dominicaine en match de préparation aux JO |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-equipe-de-france-olympique-corrige-la-republique-dominicaine-en-match-amical/1481902 |website=L'Equipe |access-date=11 July 2024 |archive-date=11 July 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240711213901/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-equipe-de-france-olympique-corrige-la-republique-dominicaine-en-match-amical/1481902 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 24 July, during France's Olympic opener against the [[United States men's national under-23 soccer team|United States]], he scored a goal, contributing to the team's 3–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.lequipe.fr/Jo-2024-paris/Football/Actualites/L-equipe-de-france-reussit-son-entree-aux-jo-2024-face-aux-etats-unis/1484968 | title = L'équipe de France réussit son entrée aux JO 2024 face aux États-Unis | language = fr | website = L'Équipe | date = 24 July 2024 | first= Mickaël | last = Duché | access-date = 25 July 2024}}</ref> He ended the tournament with two goals and five assists as France finished runners-up, winning the silver medal.

===Senior===
On 29 August 2024, Olise was called up to the senior [[France national football team|France national team]] for the first time by manager [[Didier Deschamps]], for their matches against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] and [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] in the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]].<ref>{{cite web |date=31 August 2023 |title=La liste des vingt-trois Bleus |trans-title=The twenty-three Blues |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/13073-la-liste-des-vingt-trois-bleus.html |access-date=30 August 2024 |website=fff.fr |publisher=[[French Football Federation]] |language=fr |archive-date=30 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240830091657/https://www.fff.fr/article/13073-la-liste-des-vingt-trois-bleus.html |url-status=live }}</ref> He made his debut on 6 September against Italy at the [[Parc des Princes]], starting the game and playing 58 minutes in a 3–1 loss.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Italy 3-1 France (Sep 6, 2024) Final Score |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698898/italy-france |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=ESPN |language=en |archive-date=6 September 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240906211955/https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698898/italy-france |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 23 March 2025, he scored his first senior goal for France in a 2–0 win over [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in the second leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League A#Quarter-finals|Nations League quarter-finals]], also recording an assist to help his side overturn a two-goal aggregate deficit and advance to the next stage of the competition.<ref>{{Cite web |title=France 2-0 Croatia (2-2 agg, 5-4 on pens): France scrape through into Nations League semi-finals |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c70e7y626ejt |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=22 March 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250322203624/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c70e7y626ejt |url-status=live }}</ref> During the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals|Nations League Finals]] on 8 June, he netted in a 2–0 victory against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in the third place play-off.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Germany 0-2 France |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c75390g2rpgt |date=8 June 2025 |access-date=23 July 2025 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB }}</ref>

On 11 May 2026, he was named in the France squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/france-world-cup-squad-named |access-date=2026-05-27 |website=www.fifa.com}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Olise possesses a range of passing skills, which he can often use to play behind the opposition's defence or switch the angle of attack. He likes to operate 50 to 30 yards out from goal in the right half-space, where he can use various options to continue the attack. Though mainly left footed, Olise is also capable of scoring with either of his feet.<ref>{{Cite web|date=27 July 2021|title=Michael Olise Scout Report: How Crystal Palace's big signing from Reading can help Vieira get off to a good start|url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/analysis/michael-olise-crystal-palace-2020-21-scout-report-tactical-analysis-tactics|access-date=25 January 2022|website=Total Football Analysis Magazine|language=en-GB|archive-date=25 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220125235502/https://totalfootballanalysis.com/analysis/michael-olise-crystal-palace-2020-21-scout-report-tactical-analysis-tactics|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="breakthrough">{{Cite web |title=Michael Olise: Reading's breakthrough teenager |url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/article/michael-olise-readings-breakthrough-teenager-tactical-analysis-tactics |access-date=26 January 2022 |website=Total Football Analysis Magazine |date=19 January 2021 |language=en-GB |archive-date=26 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220126000402/https://totalfootballanalysis.com/article/michael-olise-readings-breakthrough-teenager-tactical-analysis-tactics |url-status=live }}</ref>

On the ball, Olise is an agile and mobile player. He is capable of turning quickly with good acceleration and change of pace, even when he is dribbling in very tight spaces or running with the ball.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Michael Olise: Reading's breakthrough teenager |url=https://totalfootballanalysis.com/article/michael-olise-readings-breakthrough-teenager-tactical-analysis-tactics |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Total Football Analysis |date=19 January 2021 |language=en-GB}}</ref> In an interview with Bayern Munich's magazine ''51'', Olise spoke of his idolisation for [[Neymar]] as a child, stating that he "liked his tricky style of play. You learn things from lots of players, though - that way you become complete."<ref name=":2" />

==Personal life==
Olise's younger brother [[Richard Olise|Richard]] is also a footballer and joined [[Chelsea F.C. Under-21s and Academy|Chelsea]] as an Under-19, representing England at youth level.<ref>{{cite web |title=Michael Olise To Represent France At Toulon Tournament |url=https://thetilehurstend.sbnation.com/2019/5/27/18641427/michael-olise-to-represent-france-at-toulon-tournament-reading-fc-royals |website=thetilehurstend.sbnation.com/ |publisher=The Tilehurst End |access-date=27 May 2019 |date=27 May 2019 |archive-date=29 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220129135830/https://thetilehurstend.sbnation.com/2019/5/27/18641427/michael-olise-to-represent-france-at-toulon-tournament-reading-fc-royals |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite wearing [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]] boots, Olise does not have a personal sponsorship with any equipment manufacturers.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Discret hors terrain, pas de contrat avec un équipementier, égérie d'aucune marque : Olise, l'anti-star des Bleus |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Discret-hors-terrain-pas-de-contrat-avec-un-equipementier-egerie-d-aucune-marque-olise-l-anti-star-des-bleus/1600394 |access-date=8 April 2026 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> Olise is known for his shy, reserved demeanour and his dislike of giving media interviews.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Adams |first=Tom |date=9 April 2026 |title=Thierry Henry praises Michael Olise's demeanor, attention to detail after Bayern Munich beat Real Madrid |url=https://www.bavarianfootballworks.com/champions-league/186806/thierry-henry-praises-michael-olises-demeanor-attention-to-detail-after-bayern-munich-beat-real-madrid |access-date=27 April 2026 |website=Bavarian Football Works |language=en-US}}</ref>

